---
import { centerDrops, commands, guidePages, netherIslands, safetyRules, upgrades } from "../data/wiki";

const { page } = Astro.props;
const slug = page.slug;
const related = guidePages.filter((item) => item.slug !== slug).slice(0, 3);
---

{
	slug === "getting-started" && (
		<>
			<section class="band">
				<h2>First Steps</h2>
			</section>
			<article class="article search-card" data-search={page.search}>
				<header>
					<p>{page.category}</p>
					<h2>Getting Started</h2>
				</header>
				<div class="section-copy">
					<h3>Your First Island</h3>
					<p>
						When you join, Mineperial creates your Skyblock island and sends you there. The
						island starts with grass, dirt, a tree, a protected lodestone core, and a starter chest.
					</p>
					<ul>
						<li>Starter chest: lava bucket, ice, oak saplings, bone meal, bread, dirt, cobblestone, and string.</li>
						<li>Use <code>/msb island</code> to check your island coordinates.</li>
						<li>Use <code>/setspawn</code> while standing on your island to set your return point.</li>
						<li>Your island core uses lodestone and bedrock protection, so do not plan builds that require removing it.</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
			</article>
		</>
	)
}

{
	slug === "commands" && (
		<>
			<section class="band">
				<h2>Member Commands</h2>
			</section>
			<article class="article search-card" data-search={page.search}>
				<header>
					<p>{page.category}</p>
					<h2>Commands</h2>
				</header>
				<p class="section-copy">
					These are the Skyblock commands exposed to regular members. Staff-only maintenance commands are intentionally left out.
				</p>
				<div class="table-wrap">
					<table>
						<thead>
							<tr>
								<th>Command</th>
								<th>What It Does</th>
							</tr>
						</thead>
						<tbody>
							{
								commands.map(([command, description]) => (
									<tr>
										<td><code>{command}</code></td>
										<td>{description}</td>
									</tr>
								))
							}
						</tbody>
					</table>
				</div>
			</article>
		</>
	)
}

{
	slug === "teams" && (
		<>
			<section class="band">
				<h2>Shared Islands</h2>
			</section>
			<article class="article search-card" data-search={page.search}>
				<header>
					<p>{page.category}</p>
					<h2>Teams</h2>
				</header>
				<p class="section-copy">
					Teams let several players share one island. The leader owns the shared island, manages invites,
					and controls team-only actions such as renaming or kicking.
				</p>
				<div class="steps">
					<div>
						<span>1</span>
						<h3>Create</h3>
						<p>Use <code>/team create &lt;name&gt;</code>. Names can use letters, numbers, spaces, or hyphens, and must be 3-24 characters.</p>
					</div>
					<div>
						<span>2</span>
						<h3>Invite</h3>
						<p>Team leaders can use <code>/team invite &lt;player&gt;</code>. The player must be online and not already on a team.</p>
					</div>
					<div>
						<span>3</span>
						<h3>Accept</h3>
						<p>Accepting joins the leader's island. The accepting player's old solo island is wiped.</p>
					</div>
					<div>
						<span>4</span>
						<h3>Leave</h3>
						<p>Members who leave or get kicked receive a fresh island. If a leader leaves a multi-player team, leadership transfers.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</article>
		</>
	)
}

{
	slug === "upgrades" && (
		<>
			<section class="band">
				<h2>Generator Upgrades</h2>
			</section>
			<article class="article search-card" data-search={page.search}>
				<header>
					<p>{page.category}</p>
					<h2>Generator Menu</h2>
				</header>
				<p class="section-copy">
					Open <code>/msb upgrades</code> to spend Center Shards and materials. Generator upgrades affect
					cobblestone or stone that forms from your generator.
				</p>
				<div class="upgrade-grid">
					{
						upgrades.map((upgrade) => (
							<section>
								<div>
									<h3>{upgrade.name}</h3>
									<code>/msb upgrades buy {upgrade.buy}</code>
								</div>
								<p>{upgrade.effect}</p>
								<dl>
									<div>
										<dt>Cost</dt>
										<dd>{upgrade.cost}</dd>
									</div>
									<div>
										<dt>Note</dt>
										<dd>{upgrade.note}</dd>
									</div>
								</dl>
							</section>
						))
					}
				</div>
			</article>
		</>
	)
}

{
	slug === "center" && (
		<>
			<section class="band">
				<h2>The Center</h2>
			</section>
			<article class="article search-card" data-search={page.search}>
				<header>
					<p>{page.category}</p>
					<h2>Asteroid Field</h2>
				</header>
				<div class="split">
					<div>
						<p>
							The center is the asteroid field around world spawn. It is the main place to earn
							Center Shards, mine renewable resource veins, find crates, and fight other players.
						</p>
						<ul>
							<li>Center radius: about 160 blocks from 0,0.</li>
							<li>PvP is enabled inside the center.</li>
							<li>Regular resource veins respawn after about 15 minutes.</li>
							<li>Center events last 20 minutes and add bonus nodes plus event crates.</li>
						</ul>
					</div>
					<div class="stat-card">
						<h3>Event Loot</h3>
						<p>
							Events add 12 bonus nodes and 5 crates. Event crates can include 4-7 Center Shards
							plus items like diamonds, golden apples, XP bottles, ender pearls, and amethyst shards.
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="table-wrap compact">
					<table>
						<thead>
							<tr>
								<th>Vein</th>
								<th>Drop</th>
							</tr>
						</thead>
						<tbody>
							{
								centerDrops.map(([node, drop]) => (
									<tr>
										<td>{node}</td>
										<td>{drop}</td>
									</tr>
								))
							}
						</tbody>
					</table>
				</div>
			</article>
		</>
	)
}

{
	slug === "nether" && (
		<>
			<section class="band">
				<h2>Nether Archipelago</h2>
			</section>
			<article class="article search-card" data-search={page.search}>
				<header>
					<p>{page.category}</p>
					<h2>Custom Nether</h2>
				</header>
				<p class="section-copy">
					The Nether is locked until staff unlocks it for the SMP. Once unlocked, Nether portals
					send you to a custom void archipelago instead of normal Nether terrain.
				</p>
				<div class="list-grid">
					{
						netherIslands.map(([name, description]) => (
							<section>
								<h3>{name}</h3>
								<p>{description}</p>
							</section>
						))
					}
				</div>
				<div class="note-row">
					<p>Nether resource nodes respawn after about 20 minutes.</p>
					<p>Ancient debris nodes respawn after about 2 hours, with only a few active at once.</p>
					<p>Bastion hotspots are PvP zones and give doubled drops from most Nether nodes.</p>
				</div>
			</article>
		</>
	)
}

{
	slug === "end" && (
		<>
			<section class="band">
				<h2>The End</h2>
			</section>
			<article class="article search-card" data-search={page.search}>
				<header>
					<p>{page.category}</p>
					<h2>Shared Dragon Arena</h2>
				</header>
				<div class="section-copy">
					<p>
						The End is locked until staff unlocks it. When it opens, a shared End portal appears
						at the center. Everyone uses the same void arena and dragon fight.
					</p>
					<ul>
						<li>The entry platform is obsidian near the arena edge.</li>
						<li>The arena is a round End Stone island with obsidian pillars and crystals.</li>
						<li>The dragon stays active and targets nearby survival or adventure players.</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
			</article>
		</>
	)
}

{
	slug === "safety" && (
		<>
			<section class="band">
				<h2>Safety And Rules</h2>
			</section>
			<article class="article search-card" data-search={page.search}>
				<header>
					<p>{page.category}</p>
					<h2>Player Safety</h2>
				</header>
				<ul class="rule-list">
					{safetyRules.map((rule) => <li>{rule}</li>)}
				</ul>
			</article>
		</>
	)
}

<section class="band">
	<h2>Related Pages</h2>
</section>

<section class="browse-grid" aria-label="Related wiki pages">
	{
		related.map((item) => (
			<a class="browse-card search-card" href={`/${item.slug}/`} data-search={`${item.title} ${item.text} ${item.search}`}>
				<img class="mc-icon" src={item.icon} alt="" />
				<strong>{item.title}</strong>
				<small>{item.text}</small>
			</a>
		))
	}
</section>
